@startuml frame-validation-diagnostic
' Requirements: L1-SDL-002, L2-SDL-005
' Source: docs/specs/space-data-link-protocol/L1.md, docs/specs/space-data-link-protocol/L2.md
title Transfer Frame Validation Failure Diagnostic (all frame families)
autonumber

actor "Ground Station" as GS
participant "UDP Frame Link" as UDP
participant "Data Link Manager" as DLM
participant "Frame Decoder" as FD
participant "Diagnostic Recorder" as DR
database "Event Log" as EL
participant "Subscription Manager" as SM
participant "WebSocket API" as WS
actor "Operator/Client" as OP

== Malformed frame received ==
GS -> UDP : UDP datagram (malformed transfer frame octets)
activate UDP
UDP -> DLM : OnFrameReceived(rawFrame, linkId, receiveTime)
deactivate UDP
activate DLM
DLM -> FD : Decode(rawFrame, missionProfile)
activate FD
note right of FD
  Frame Decoder is the profile-selected decoder
  (TM 132.0-B, AOS 732.0-B, USLP 732.1-B or TC 232.0-B).
end note
FD -> FD : Validation fails (e.g. FECF CRC mismatch, length\nmismatch, unknown SCID/VCID, bad version number)
FD --> DLM : FrameValidationError(reason, byteOffset, parsedHeaderFields)
deactivate FD

== Explicit diagnostic emission (no silent frame loss) ==
DLM -> DR : Report(validationError, frameContext)
activate DR
note right of DR
  frameContext: linkId, receiveTime, frame family,
  SCID/VCID when parseable, raw frame hex snapshot.
end note
DR -> EL : Append(diagnostic { severity=ERROR, reason, frameContext })
DR -> SM : Publish(LinkDiagnosticEvent)
activate SM
SM -> WS : Push(linkDiagnosticEvent) to subscribed sessions
activate WS
WS -> OP : link event: frame rejected (reason, frame context)
deactivate WS
deactivate SM
DR --> DLM : diagnosticId
deactivate DR
DLM -> DLM : Increment rejectedFrames counter for linkId;\ndrop frame (attributably, never silently)
deactivate DLM

note over DLM, EL
  AC L2-SDL-005: GIVEN a malformed transfer frame WHEN validation
  executes THEN an error diagnostic is recorded with failure reason
  and frame context. (L1-SDL-002: no silent frame loss.)
end note
@enduml
